Vice President Mike Pence announced that he will be traveling to Central and South America in August on behalf of President Trump. He will visit Cartagena and Bogota in Colombia, Buenos Aires in Argentina, Santiago in Chile, and Panama City in Panama. The purpose of the trip is to strengthen bilateral trade and investment ties, support security cooperation, business engagement, agriculture, and infrastructure development. The trip is seen as a sign of the high importance that President Trump places on the region. More details about the trip will be released later.